        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "refactor: centralize inbound supplemental context",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nMoves more inbound context responsibility into core. Channel plugins now pass canonical supplemental/facts payloads; core owns visibility filtering, media payload projection, lazy quote-media merge, self-reply suppression, and legacy prompt-field projection.\n\nWhat changed:\n\n- `finalizeInboundContext` accepts `MsgContext.SupplementalContext` and projects it into existing `ReplyTo*`, `Forwarded*`, `Thread*`, `GroupSystemPrompt`, and untrusted-context fields before prompt normalization.\n- `finalizeChannelInboundContext` centralizes supplemental filtering, media payload merge, optional async quote-media resolution, self-quote body/media suppression, injected finalizer support, and hidden quote/forward/thread diagnostics.\n- `buildChannelInboundEventContext` routes through the core finalizer while preserving the public sync/async SDK contract: sync by default, `Promise` only for `resolveSupplementalMedia: true`.\n- Bundled/internal channel callers moved to `buildChannelInboundEventContext` or `runtime.channel.turn.buildContext`; direct finalizer usage is now a deprecated public compatibility island.\n- Discord and Telegram await `buildChannelInboundEventContext({ resolveSupplementalMedia: true })`; channel code still owns native fetch/parsing, core owns merge/suppression/finalization.\n- Matrix, Feishu, iMessage, WhatsApp dispatch, QQBot, Slack, MS Teams, Signal, Google Chat, Synology Chat, Tlon, Twitch, Zalo, and Zalo User now use the builder/turn-builder path for inbound context payload construction.\n- `resolveChannelInboundSupplementalContext` remains exported as a deprecated SDK wrapper for compatibility.\n- Deprecated SDK type aliases remain exported so external plugin TypeScript imports keep compiling.\n- Preserved existing legacy flat fields; supplemental projection fills missing values only.\n- Added regression coverage for WhatsApp remote-only inbound media URLs.\n\nAPI/deprecation notes:\n\n- Deprecated: `filterChannelTurnSupplementalContext` alias.\n- Deprecated: `resolveChannelInboundSupplementalContext`; prefer `buildChannelInboundEventContext({ resolveSupplementalMedia: true })` for inbound payloads.\n- Deprecated: `finalizeChannelInboundContext` for new channel code; kept for public compatibility when callers already prepared legacy prompt fields.\n- Preferred: `buildChannelInboundEventContext` / `runtime.channel.turn.buildContext` for channel inbound payloads.\n- Not deprecated: legacy `ReplyTo*`, `Forwarded*`, and `Thread*` fields. They remain runtime/template compatibility fields and are now projected by core.\n\nDiff/LOC notes:\n\n- Current PR diff vs merge-base `origin/main`: +1575 / -784, net +791.\n- Production/runtime-ish triple-dot diff, excluding tests/docs/changelog: +1088 / -553, net +535.\n- Final local dirty slice added by the last migration commit: +404 / -240 overall; prod-ish +306 / -166, net +140.\n- This is not a LOC win. The win is the ownership boundary: bundled channels stop owning prompt projection/finalization, while public SDK compatibility remains intact.\n\n## Verification\n\nLatest proof after rebase, SDK compatibility fix, and final builder migration:\n\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test-compat-1.tsbuildinfo`\n  - passed\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test-compat-2.tsbuildinfo`\n  - passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/channels/inbound-event/context.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/channel-inbound.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/inbound-dispatch.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/process-message.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor.gating.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor/inbound-processing.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor/inbound-processing.systemPrompt.test.ts extensions/matrix/src/matrix/monitor/handler.body-for-agent.test.ts extensions/msteams/src/monitor-handler/message-handler.authz.test.ts extensions/signal/src/monitor/event-handler.inbound-context.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.dm-topic-threadid.test.ts extensions/zalouser/src/monitor.group-gating.test.ts`\n  - passed: 12 files, 200 tests after final rebase on `origin/main` `9b9d8970b0`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/inbound-dispatch.test.ts`\n  - passed: 1 file, 46 tests\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/channels/inbound-event/context.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/channel-inbound.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.dm-topic-threadid.test.ts`\n  - passed: 3 files, 22 tests\n- `git diff --check`\n  - passed\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --no-web-search --output /tmp/inbound-refactor-autoreview-async-builder-3.txt --json-output /tmp/inbound-refactor-autoreview-async-builder-3.json`\n  - clean: no accepted/actionable findings; overall patch is correct\n\nEarlier focused channel proof during this refactor:\n\n- Core finalization + reply inbound tests passed: 2 files, 28 tests.\n- Matrix/MS Teams focused tests passed: 2 files, 25 tests.\n- WhatsApp inbound context/dispatch tests passed before the final regression addition: 2 files, 48 tests.\n- Signal/iMessage focused tests passed: 3 files, 48 tests.\n- Telegram focused shared-builder and media tests passed.\n- Discord focused context/process-message tests passed: 2 files, 77 tests.\n- Feishu targeted quote/thread tests passed; QQBot full outbound-dispatch tests passed.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Inbound quote/forward/thread supplemental context is filtered, media-merged, and projected consistently in core while preserving channel-specific parsing, fetches, routing metadata, SDK sync/async compatibility, and Discord/Telegram self-reply suppression behavior.\n\nReal environment tested: Local source checkout with focused core, plugin SDK, QQBot, WhatsApp, and representative rich-channel Vitest suites plus core/extension test typecheck.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: See `Verification` above; latest commands were run after the rebase, SDK compatibility restoration, and WhatsApp remote-only media regression fix.\n\nEvidence after fix: Focused tests passed for core finalization, SDK exports, Discord, Telegram, WhatsApp, Signal, iMessage, Matrix, MS Teams, Feishu, QQBot, and Zalo User surfaces; local autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings after fixing SDK compatibility and WhatsApp remote-media findings.\n\nObserved result after fix: Channels pass canonical `SupplementalContext`/facts or builder facts into core; `finalizeInboundContext` projects legacy fields once; lazy reply media is resolved by the finalizer path only when visible and not self-suppressed; remote-only WhatsApp inbound media URLs remain present in finalized context.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full repository test suite, full CI completion, and live channel roundtrips were not run for this refactor PR.\n",
